  "texts": [
    "The sample was balanced by keyword prevalence and publishers (Uued Uudised and Ekspress Grupp), but not by the time or source article.",
    "Based on annotator feedback, we removed very long, repetitive or listlike and non-topical sentences, leaving 7345 sentences.",
    "The sentences were annotated on a 1-5 point scale from pro-to anti-immigration, with the option to mark the sentence as ambiguous instead.",
    "Ratings were later reduced to four classes of Against (1-2), Neutral (3), Supportive (4-5), and Ambiguous.",
    "Annotators were instructed to classify sentences expressing supportive or positive attitude as Supportive and the opposite as Against."
  ],
